title: Dakota pipeline protesters leave site after year-long occupation
text:
Media playback is unsupported on your device Dakota pipeline protesters leave site after year-long occupation 23 February 2017 Last updated at 09:37 GMT 
A year-long protest against an oil pipeline in North Dakota appears to be nearing its end, as a government deadline for demonstrators to leave the area passes. 
Some demonstrators who ignored requests to depart were arrested, and makeshift wooden structures were set ablaze. Read more
